text: Alright, so here's some general info for KingCon tmr I wanted to throw out there. Make sure to set up both computers tomorrow, one will have both our CAD (Maybe last year's its nicer) and code pulled up, the other will display our social media card linked below. The QR code on that takes you directly to the boosters donation page, which has a form to fill out, make sure they denote robotics as the club to donate too. In addition, someone needs to bring a tip jar of sorts for cash donations. The deal with the keychains, both hazen and NES, is that they're free with any donation. Possibly make a little sign for that if you'd like. If someone asks for a suggested amount, say 5 or 10 dollars. As for the robot demo, if technicolor is running, have it on the ground and a DS set up. Let people shoot all 8 rings into the goal, score it according to ftc and keep a highscore sheet. If they break the high score, ask them if they'd be interested in winning the laser thing if they keep that score till sunday, and get contact info if they do.
